## 4. Code Structure Explanation

### Student.java

Purpose:
Represents a student object.

Attributes:

* studentId
* name
* age
* grade
* contact

Responsibilities:

* Store student information
* Provide getters and setters
* Display student details
* Convert object into file storage format

---

### StudentManager.java

Purpose:
Handles all business logic.

Responsibilities:

* Add student
* View all students
* Search by ID
* Search by name
* Update records
* Delete records
* Manage ArrayList<Student>

---

### ValidationUtils.java

Purpose:
Validates user input.

Responsibilities:

* Validate age
* Validate grade
* Validate student ID
* Validate name
* Validate contact information

---

### FileHandler.java

Purpose:
Manages file operations.

Responsibilities:

* Save student data to file
* Load student data from file
* Handle file-related exceptions

---

### StudentInformationSystem.java

Purpose:
Main application entry point.

Responsibilities:

* Display menu
* Handle user input
* Connect all classes together
* Execute CRUD operations

